caption: Really fresh and great tasting empanadas.
Best flavor best empanadas but way too expensive now went from 3.50 to now 6 dollars each thats just way too much 😅  I suggest making them your self
Un Delicious, not fresh  not recommend

I went today and it was delicious. The two Jamaican patties I consumed were delicious. I did get the green sauce but unfortunately one of them had little specs of mold on it. Overall, my experience was great.

Absolutely the best Chilean Empanadas other than from Santiago Chile.  As a kid I travelled to Chile to visit family and always craved the empanadas.  This place does it right.  Perfect dough and the meat/onion filling along with egg and olive is perfect.  The other empanadas they offer are good but I’m all about the Chilean ones.  This place is killer and hope it can stay alive through the pandemic. I travel to DC for work on occasion and the last time (about a month ago) had lunch to go and a took a half dozen home to freeze.  Just reheated my last one and already making plans to go back.  Even pre COVID it’s a buy and go type of place.  Enjoy and stay safe!
Yummy yummy yummy yummy yummy
The service was sociable and attentive.
Great authentic empanadas!!! The whole family enjoyed them—even our extremely picky 7 year old!

I've had Julia's Empanadas in the past and they were great! but today I asked the person at the desk if the Chicken empanada's had peas - he told me no. Bite into the empanada and it has peas - i'm allergic, luckily nothing major but I explicitly asked before purchasing and then wasn't able to eat them. I ordered 4 different types of empanada's and my family and I all agreed that they had no significant flavor profile. I might try again but never buying more than one especially when I can't be told proper ingredients.

Maybe it was that batch, but the four empanadas - including saltenas,chorizos, chilean and Jamaican we tried were barely flavorful. i won't mind giving this place a second chance. Also the place only takes credit cards if the total purchase is $10+ but the machine wasn't working   that day.
Steak and cilantro a solid 4 stars. Strawberry cream cheese was a 2 star
I love those empanadas!! Been coming here for years.
Ok kinda overrated

I did not like what I witnessed.  When I was purchasing an empanada, the guy behind the register 1) did not put gloves on to handle them and 2) used the same parchment paper-- which was already laying over the empanadas -- to handle them with his dirty bare hands. I called him out on it and told him he needs to grab a new sheet for every one he touches as he bags them. That being said, he put the same parchment paper that he touched with his bare hands--even after handling money--right back in the existing rack over the empanadas. In the days of COVID-19, this is especially unacceptable.

The food was amazing and the employees were very nice. I will definitely be going back. I do have a comment, however, one of the other patrons smelled like a week old filet of fish. I think there should be signs up that say, if you smell like seafood you must order delivery. My wife of 35 years, Betty, didn’t seem to mind the smell but she grew up in cape cod so probably used to the stench of fish. This is why we are having issues in our marriage. I don’t know where this country went wrong, this new generation doesn’t care if they smell bad. Soap is not that expensive!!!! Also, the best empanada is definitely the jamaican one! Highly recommend.
Had a spinach empanada, ordered 2. The outside was white. Inside doughy and undercooked. A few years ago this was the to go spot, but its recently been a hit or miss.

A must stop place on every visit to DC
Food menu was good. Excellent food. Staff were nice.
Delicious Chilean Style Beef Empanadas (Empanadas Chilenas de carne). $6 dollars each one (plus taxes obviously).

Go to spot in the dmv area for empanadas!! They are SO GOOD, especially the Jamaican and Chilean ones 🤤  There's a $10 minimum for credit cards but there is an atm inside the store (which is tiny) or you can just buy multiple empanadas (as u should) and FEAST  They are also open very late on Saturdays and right near the dupont bars making it a great night out snack!
Good food

HORRIBLE TASTING!  Poor quality.  The filling is disgusting.  Everything is made with shortening.  The savory empanadas are as bad as the sweet empanadas, I was able to have two bites of the chicken salteña unlike the sweet empanada, I had a tiny bite and the smell alone made me gag.  I can’t even begin to understand why they are still in business. Poor representation of the true empanadas. Unless you are drunk and hungry, avoid this place.
Quick delicious food
Bomb empanadas! Come here for the night cap munchies
Nice little spot in a busy area. We stopped in one evening and picked up a few empanadas. All were cooked perfectly. My favorite was the chorizo. The Chilean was also a hit. Will definitely go back.
Good empanadas, fast service. 4/5 because the prices $24 for 3 empanadas and a water, it's DC but still sizes are not big.

The most amazing empanada spot there is. These guys started a deep love between empanadas and I 20 years ago when my sister lived down the street on California Ave. Fresh, delicious, and their salsa is fantastic on them. You can't go wrong and the dessert ones are all great too!
Stumbled across here by walking the wrong way, so glad we did.  Chorizo Empanada was awesome!!
Price: taste=4 stars I got guava and pear, almond and pear and one vegan one. All were tasty, but the guava one was especially good. My meat loving friends loved the Jamaican one and the spinach one

Love these empanadas! A little hard to spot this local mom and pop shop but once you find it you'll always remember to come back. Limited options but each are tasty! Grab one and go people watch on the sidewalk as you enjoy the DC vibes.

The empanadas are pretty good. Only can talk about the savory ones. We only wished they were a bit smaller so we could try a few instead of having to settle for one. The lunch combos are a good deal. The soup was tasty too.

The Jamaican patty and Chilean empanadas are excellent. In fact, the Chilean one was too perfect not to be made by a Chilean. Can now confirm the owner is from Chile. These really brought back memories of my summer trips as a child. The dough is soft and mince meat is sweet and savory with raisins and olives. Perfection!
Chilean empanadas are the best!
Yum! Can't wait to try more next time!

Super rude front desk guy, as other reviews have stated.  Very awkward, not even worth walking in.  Told me "Get out of my store" after telling him to keep the change.  Don't know what else to say I think that speaks for itself.
Excellent empanadas in a no frills takeout spot. We enjoyed them in a park across the street. Wide variety. Would have been nice if there was a simple cheese option for the kids though.

They are all good. Whether it's the chilean, the salteña, the jamaican, the spinach or the daily veggie special, you can't go wrong with any of them! They are always freshly made and always keep that homestyle flavor.

Loved them
Delicious, well made, and a family favorite
Had two empanadas for quick lunch. Awesome and delicious. Perfect for a snack. 5star taste :)

I was so excited to try this place. I was so disappointed. First the dude working was super rude. I ordered an empanada in Spanish i said me da una salteña” and pointed at it. He yelled “English please!” So loud for that tiny place that it startled me. I apologized and said the same thing with less words he wrapped up the empanada. The empanada was big, not the worst but not good either. It was dry. The outside was so crunchy that it reminded me of a crouton. I will not be returning.
Superb in taste so many variety.
Convenient late night snack. Tourist friendly

Went during lunch hour rush. They were fast and the food was oh so good.

Wow! Amazing empanadas! Tried 4 different flavors, and all were excellent: Saltena, Chilean, Turkey and Chorizo. The Saltena had green bell peppers which was not listed in the ingredients but did not overwhelm the flavor, which was excellent. The Chilean is the favorite empanada here, was recommended by the staff, and it did not disappoint. Not very spicy, but very flavorful, with a zest that will leave you wanting more. Cash only spot, but worth the trip to the ATM.
Great food, I went there on 4/26 around 8pm. Staff was extremely rude and decided to ignore us to talk to his friend on the phone. Then proceeded to sing song lyrics while we were trying to order.
Five of these empanadas (2 spinach, 1 pineapple custard, 1 apple, 1 chorizo) carried me 9 miles on the White Oak Canyon hike. I'll be carrying many of these back to NYC with me. Highly recommend!
The Jamaican and Chilean empanadas are the best ones! I also recommend the hot sauce.
Delightful homemade empanadas!
They need to do better with their empanadas. They use to be very good now their items are not tasty anymore.
Super tasty and cheap empenadas. Beware they do run out at the end of the night. Great option for a cold night.
Very good food

Hot and fresh empenadas to go, plus some accessory sides. Don't expect more cuz that's about it! They're good, they're hot, and they're probably the cheapest meal you're likely to find around Dupont.
Wow! We both loved the empanada with Jamaican filling, chorizo a close second. I'll definitely go back the next time we're in town.
Hole in the wall but Empanadas are amazing!
Friendly service for authentic and delicious empanadas. They get the masa just right. The Chilenos are my favorite but the Salteñas are great too.

Empenadas as $5, usually ready to order, hot and delicious. By far some of my favorite empenadas, with about 6 flavors, including a veggie option. My favorite is the Jamaica/curry. I've only been at night. If you're going after 11pm try to get there before the club let out. It'll save you a lot of time as the line forms quickly.
Every time in in D.C gotta get one!
Didn't get what I ordered. Noticed after getting back to hotel. What I did get a fruit pastry was stale.

This place has some seriously good food and I would definitely recommend it if you are in the area. The empanadas here are HUGE, I have pretty sizable hands and they were bigger than that. They are also reasonably priced as well. The apple desert empanada was very good as well as the two savory ones that I had chorizo with beans and rice along with Jamaican.  I preferred the Jamaican one to the chorizo one.

Went to Julia's empanada today and I was so disappointed. The cost was a bit much. I paid eleven dollars for two empanada.The spinich empanada taste solely of spinich and I ordered a Chirzo empanada and got nothing but rice and beans. Yuck .I Definately had better at Bahamas breeze.
Bomb
The empanadas at Julia's are very very good and at a great price. No doubt the best quality to price ratio we found in DC. Don't miss it!
Some of the best empanadas I've had. Love there chorizo, Jamaican, and Chilean.
Soooo yummy. The Jamaican empanada was delicious. 😋
Tasty empanadas. I especially enjoyed the turkey one I had. Great seasoning and not too much bread!

Considering how long this place has been here, it's slightly impressive that their empanadas have been consistent decent after all this time. It's quick and the price is okay, $5 per empanada. I would say that some of their empanadas are definitely better than others, but if you're looking for something homemade and quick this is the place!
I think the prices go up every year ($5 for one empanada?) but it’s great for something handmade and quick.

These are the best empanadas on the East Coast USA in Danna’s judgement. As I think about to - never have had an empanada on the West Coast so can say best in the USA. Well worth a stop if you’re an empanada fan. They do get dinged a star for being a little on the dingy side. Needs coat of paint -not old like it cool and hip just as in place needs some attention. But still! Worth the stop!

Very pretty looking pastries, but mostly empty and WAY overpriced. It was about 8pm. I got a pear almond pastry. There was almost no filling. Tasted kind of like almond extract but it was mostly dried up pastry dough. For $3 + tip, I was not impressed at all. I threw most of it away because I’m already fat and I don’t need to waste my daily calories on plain dough. Sorry, Julia. Maybe it was just an off day or something but I’ve had better empanadas at Taco Bell, for $1.
Huge delicious empanadas! Except for The peach almond empanada which was a bit doughy and I would skip the chorizo w/rice and beans !

Delicious, massive empanadas!
Never good to eat after a night of drinking. Save yourself the tummy ache.
Great place to go when you're a bit tipsy and need some calories. We tried 6 different flavors, everything was yummy.

The service was great.  The empanadas were diverse and fairly tasty.  I tried four varieties and found two to be far above average, but in general the crusts were heavy, and thus the fillings were flavorful but the ensemble a bit subdued.  The prices were also a bit rich to eat 4...

An establishment for many years, they produce reliable and pretty large empanadas. The price has jumped a bit over the years, from $3 to now $5.50, but they are still worth it. The place is a pocket, so don't think you will do more than order, receive and run. Great late night bite - open till 4AM on the weekend.  Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz
Julia's has the best empanadas I've ever had. Try the "Jamaican style" one, with ground beef and olives, and the one with shredded chicken.
the best place in the city to get a quick bite. one empanada, $5 is a full, filling meal.

Yum! I don't have much empanada experience to compare these by but they were good. The Chilean one was the one I tried. Really filling and cheap! Don’t let the short review fool you this is one of my favorite places to go anywhere in the DC area for food. Places like this are also the reason why I started to write about the food I get when I travel.  I normally go for the chicken curry and a Peruvian beef empanadas.
Great drunk food!!!
Great food. Really enjoyed our lunch. Went a day that was raining found out it is only takeout.

Great local shop and great prices. When I travel to DC for business, this is always my first stop. Take out only and can get pretty crowded, but the line always move quickly.

Perfect spot to go to pre the club or post the club and you need to sober up. The empanadas are really good and really filling! I love the empanadas with fruit and cheese in them and they have really great savory options. Bring cash!

We walked to Dupont Circle twice for these empanadas! My fav is the Chilean while my friend likes the Jamaican. They are large and filling and flavorful. The young guy at night is brusque (likely bcz he doesn't want to be there) but the two older gentlemen in the morning are friendly and awesome. They even threw in a free drink for us.
Friend #1: that was really good. Friend $2: delicious Friend #3: mehh..theyre good.  Peruvian, not Chilean.

Went here late with some friends after karaoke on a Tuesday. The guy was a bit unfriendly as I asked about what I could add onto the meal to get to the credit card minimum as I did not have any cash on me. I thought it was illegal to require a minimum card amount. The empanada was ok. I liked that there was a vegan option. But I probably won't go back. The guy working was fairly rude.

Amazing empanadas.  I have to say they are some of the best in town.  Lovely staff and fast service.  One or two will keep you very full.  I love the chicken saltena.

Simple menu and good ingredients make these empanadas delicious. I tried the spinach empanada, and then some fruit empanadas for dessert. Excellent quality, great service. I went in before lunch and I didn't have to wait in line.
Amazing hearty food, staff is always super friendly and quick. They're open late too!
new to town from Atlanta. They guy was super friendly and the veggie empanada and other people there claimed this is where they come all the time to get the best empanadas...love it
Empanadas have good flavor, great for after a late night at the bars.

The best late night, post drinks, I've got the munchies food.

Who would have thought that empenadas made such a great drunk food? Well whoever it was is a genius because I ate like 3 of these bad boys at 2 in the morning. It was crowded, but the line moves fast, and the empenadas are ready to go. Plus it's not hard on the wallet. I'd go again during my next late night in dupont.

The BEST Chilean empanadas I have had in the US. Very authentic taste/flavor. I wish I had bought a few dozen to take home. This is a must stop for lunch/food on the go. SO GOOD. Cant wait to come back and get more. Amazed.
Julia's is a must if you are visiting DC. The Salteña and Jamaican are among my favorites. They open late if you go out in the area.

I've stop here from time to time after working out to grab a quick snack. Delicious!

Cheap and dirty, in a good way. Those empenadas were big and great. Go to place for a midnight snack or the end of a night of drinking

Love this place! If you like Empanadas they have a wide selection. I prefer the curry chicken and the dessert Empanadas are great. The best part is though you can actually feed a family here in DC for about 2o bucks at this place.

Really good at what they're doing. It's late at night, you're hungry, Julia's Empanadas are the place to go. When I came, there was no line but I saw a group of people outside the shop eating the empanadas. My friend and I stepped into the small shop, which was small in size but smelled amazing. The empanadas were on display in the case, and the menu was simple and easy to navigate through on the wall.  I ordered the chorizo empanada, which was crispy, golden brown on the outside and chewy, meaty goodness on the inside: just what I expected. I would give a 3, but the customer service was quick and patient  that this little shop deserves a 4. Definitely gonna visit here if I'm in town.

Delicious, warm, handmade empanadas and excellent friendly customer service. My boyfriend and I liked this place so much we ate there twice in one day. The Chorizo and Jamaican were our favorite, but all of them looked delicious.

Flaky and crispy, stuffed with goodness.  Short walk from Metro rail.  Definitely worth the trip.  We'll be making a second trip downtown this week just to go here again.  Bring cash unless you plan on spending $10.

After spending 20 minutes looking for parking, having to deal with a rude guy selling the empanadas, I was at least hopeful that the empanadas were going to be out of this world.  I love empanadas in a huge way unfortunately  the ones sold at this establishment were not good at all not only for me but for my wife as well. A staple in DC cheap eats. Two handfuls to choose from & they're all delectable. Recommendation: Jamaican.

When you need a quick bite after a night out, not much beats this DC staple.

OMG I love Julia's empanadas! So good! I love it so much! The empanadas are big and filling and delicious and moist and perfect and they don't need any sauce for dryness. They are so flavorful. Fabulous in every way. Thanks Julia, whoever you are!
Great food
I think the curried chicken and spinach empanadas are the best. Whenever I'm close I like to stop in and pick one up.
great but no beet salad
Awesome little place. Perfect for a quick lunch. Very fast.

Could be more selections but I guess they'd rather be great at somethings then OK at a lot of things. Service is quick and speedy, I don't have anything to compare with but I like coming here for lunch!
